hpnicfTeTunnel.name: hpnicfTeTunnel
hpnicfTeTunnel.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for the Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Te Tunnel.

hpnicfTeTunnelMaxTunnelIndex.name: hpnicfTeTunnelMaxTunnelIndex
hpnicfTeTunnelMaxTunnelIndex.description: The max value of tunnel id is permitted configure on the device.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspTable.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspTable
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspTable.description: This table contains information for static-crlsp, and through this to get detail information about this static-crlsp. Only support transit LSR and egress LSR.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspEntry.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspEntry
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspEntry.description: The entry in this table describes static-crlsp information.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspInLabel.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspInLabel
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspInLabel.description: This is unique label value that manualy assigned. Uniquely identifies a static-crlsp. Managers should use this to obtain detail static-crlsp information.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspName.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspName
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspName.description: The unique name assigned to the static-crlsp.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspStatus.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspStatus
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspStatus.description: Indicates the actual status of this static-crlsp, The value must be up when the static-crlsp status is up and the value must be down when the static-crlsp status is down.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspRole.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspRole
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspRole.description: This value indicate the role of this static-crlsp. This value must be transit at transit point of the tunnel, and tail at terminating point of the tunnel.

hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspXCPointer.name: hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspXCPointer
hpnicfTeTunnelStaticCrlspXCPointer.description: This pointer unique identify a row of mplsXCTable. This value should be zeroDotZero when the static-crlsp is down. The mplsXCTable identifies the segments that compose this tunnel, their characteristics, and relationships to each other.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoTable.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoTable
hpnicfTeTunnelCoTable.description: This table contains information for Co-routed reverse crlsp and infomation of Co-routed bidirectional Tunnel Interface. If hpnicfCorouteTunnelLspInstance is zero, to obtain infomation of Co-routed bidirectional Tunnel Interface, otherwise to obtain Co-routed reverse crlsp infomation.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoEntry.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoEntry
hpnicfTeTunnelCoEntry.description: The entry in this table describes Co-routed infomation of bidirectional Tunnel Interface and reserver lsp information.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoIndex.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoIndex
hpnicfTeTunnelCoIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a set of tunnel instances between a pair of ingress and egress LSRs that specified at originating point. This value should be equal to the value signaled in the Tunnel Id of the Session object.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoLspInstance.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoLspInstance
hpnicfTeTunnelCoLspInstance.description: When obtain infomation of Co-routed bidirectional Tunnel Interface, this vlaue should be zero. And this value must be LspID to obtain reverse crlsp information. Values greater than 0, but less than or equal to 65535, should be useless.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoIngressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoIngressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelCoIngressLSRId.description: Identity the ingress LSR associated with this tunnel instance. This vlaue is equal to the LsrID of originating endpoint.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoEgressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoEgressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelCoEgressLSRId.description: Identity of the egress LSR associated with this tunnel instance. This vlaue is equal to the LsrID of terminating point.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoBiMode.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoBiMode
hpnicfTeTunnelCoBiMode.description: This vlaue indicated the bidirection mode of tunnel interface. The valuemust be coroutedActive at the originating point of the tunnel and coroutedPassive at the terminating point.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspInstance.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspInstance
hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspInstance.description: This value indicated the reverse lsp instance, and should be equal to obverse lsp instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspXCPointer.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspXCPointer
hpnicfTeTunnelCoReverseLspXCPointer.description: This pointer unique index to mplsXCTable of the reverse lsp. The mplsXCTable identifies the segments that compose this tunnel, their characteristics, and relationships to each other. A value of zeroDotZero indicate that there is no crlsp assigned to this.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsTable.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsTable
hpnicfTeTunnelPsTable.description: This table defines some objects for managers to obtain TE tunnel Protection Switching group current status information.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsEntry.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsEntry
hpnicfTeTunnelPsEntry.description: The entry in this table describes TE tunnel Protection Switching group infromation.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsIndex.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsIndex
hpnicfTeTunnelPsIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a TE tunnel Protection Switching group instance. This value must be equal to the tunnel id of work tunnel instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsIngressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsIngressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelPsIngressLSRId.description: Identity the ingress LSR associated with work tunnel instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsEgressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsEgressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelPsEgressLSRId.description: Identity of the egress LSR associated with work tunnel instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIndex.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIndex
hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIndex.description: Uniquely identifies a TE tunnel Protection Switching group instance. This value must be equal to the tunnel id of TE tunnel Protection Switching group instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIngressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIngressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectIngressLSRId.description: Identity the ingress LSR associated with TE tunnel Protection Switching group instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectEgressLSRId.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectEgressLSRId
hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectEgressLSRId.description: Identity of the egress LSR associated with TE tunnel Protection Switching group instance.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectType.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectType
hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectType.description: This value indicated TE tunnel Protection Switching group type. The default value is oneToOne.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsRevertiveMode.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsRevertiveMode
hpnicfTeTunnelPsRevertiveMode.description: This value indicated protect switch mode. The value must be revertive or nonRevertive, default value is revertive.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsWtrTime.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsWtrTime
hpnicfTeTunnelPsWtrTime.description: The cycle time that switch to protect tunnel.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsHoldOffTime.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsHoldOffTime
hpnicfTeTunnelPsHoldOffTime.description: This value is switchback delay time. When detected the work path fault, switch to protect path after this time.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchMode.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchMode
hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchMode.description: This value indicated TE tunnel Protection Switching group switch mode.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsWorkPathStatus.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsWorkPathStatus
hpnicfTeTunnelPsWorkPathStatus.description: This value indicates work path status. none, noDefect, inDefect will be used.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectPathStatus.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectPathStatus
hpnicfTeTunnelPsProtectPathStatus.description: This value indicates protect path status. none, noDefect, inDefect(3) will be used.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchResult.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchResult
hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchResult.description: This value indicated current using path is work path or protect path.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchWtoP.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchWtoP
hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchWtoP.description: This notification is generated when protect workgroup switch from work tunnel to protect tunnel.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchPtoW.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchPtoW
hpnicfTeTunnelPsSwitchPtoW.description: This notification is generated when protect workgroup switch from protect tunnel to work tunnel.

hpnicfTeTunnelNotificationsGroup.name: hpnicfTeTunnelNotificationsGroup
hpnicfTeTunnelNotificationsGroup.description: This group contains MPLS Te Tunnel traps.

hpnicfTeTunnelScalarsGroup.name: hpnicfTeTunnelScalarsGroup
hpnicfTeTunnelScalarsGroup.description: Scalar object needed to implement MPLS te tunnels.

hpnicfTeTunnelCorouteGroup.name: hpnicfTeTunnelCorouteGroup
hpnicfTeTunnelCorouteGroup.description: Objects for quering Co-routed reverse crlsp information.

hpnicfTeTunnelPsGroup.name: hpnicfTeTunnelPsGroup
hpnicfTeTunnelPsGroup.description: Objects for quering protect workgroup information.
